[[File:Nagoya City Archives 2016.3.25.jpg|thumb|The Nagoya Court of Appeals building houses today the city archives]] '''Nagoya City Archives''' (名古屋市市政資料館) is a historic building located in the city of [[Nagoya]], central [[Japan]].
It was constructed in 1922 during the [[Taishō era]], when western influences in architecture were increasingly fashionable in Japan. It was originally build as the Nagoya Court of Appeals building. It is designated today as an Important Cultural Property.
